=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_BrownNoise_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A bright clean sound, with sine_like oscillator character around 50 Hz, featuring punchy attack and sustained envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, and filtered with steep_rolloff character.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: bright
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: clean
  spectral_complexity_mean: moderate
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 50.0000
  harmonic_decay_rate: -3.0248
  harmonic_regularity: 0.9223
  pitch_clarity: 9.0102
  inharmonicity: 0.0394
  type: sine_like
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -17.4256
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: BrownNoise Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/BrownNoise.html
// Tags: BrownNoise, Classes, noise
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
{ BrownNoise.ar(0.1) }.play;
{ WhiteNoise.ar(0.1) }.play;
